overview: The user initiated a request to fix multiple issues within a pull
  request, emphasizing the need to resolve breaking Vercel deployments. The
  agent systematically addressed a range of problems, including critical
  security vulnerabilities related to authentication (insecure cookie, arbitrary
  pagination, large CSV exports), various functional bugs (PDF NaN values,
  inaccurate PDF metrics, NumberField null handling, inert PDF download button,
  hardcoded user name), and validation issues (time field regex). During this
  process, the agent also resolved lint errors and updated the codebase. A
  significant development was the discovery of a critical Next.js security
  vulnerability (CVE-2025-66478), which prompted an upgrade to Next.js 16.1.1.
  This upgrade, in turn, required further adjustments to the Prisma
  configuration for compatibility with Prisma 7 and a complete overhaul of the
  ESLint setup due to the removal of the  command. Despite all
  code-level fixes and successful local builds, Vercel deployments continued to
  fail, ultimately indicating that the root cause was likely missing environment
  variables on the Vercel platform rather than a code defect.
